You may find the crumbs here: toc-styles.css and the-toc-in-distill.Rmd. Hope they will be inspirational to someone.
Judging by the {distill} issues 16, 341, 366, 420, and the Stack Overflow question it seems that there is a genuine need for some kind of a ‚Äúfloating TOC on the side‚Äù in {distill}.
In his comment, J.J. Allaire summarizes the problem:
- any change in {distill} should be linked to distll.pub web framework,
- floating TOC on the side would be tricky to implement due to specific layout ‚Äúfigures that extend into the sidebar (quite common w/ distill)‚Äù.
An optimal solution can be found within Quarto publishing system. You may try scrolling up and down and observe the collapsible sidebar navigation. HTML documents rendered with Quarto use Bootstrap 5 by default, which is not the case with distill.pub.
While we wait for a solution, you may feel tempted to try ‚Äúa poor man‚Äôs TOC‚Äù that I came up with for my use case (applied to single article).
Let me know how it goes!
